WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.218 --> 00:00:12.055
The morning God Flame has finally risen
to give us a bit of warmth. Princess.

2
00:00:13.598 --> 00:00:14.933
[door opens]

3
00:00:16.268 --> 00:00:18.103
[bells jingling]

4
00:00:19.354 --> 00:00:21.106
[Harmony] Good
morning. Your Majesty.

5
00:00:22.649 --> 00:00:24.651
[Queen Kane] It is a
beautiful day. Maghra.

6
00:00:24.734 --> 00:00:27.028
The entire city will
rejoice with you.

7
00:00:27.571 --> 00:00:31.950
It is a shame Father couldn't be here
with us to celebrate your wedding day.

8
00:00:36.162 --> 00:00:37.163
[sighs]

9
00:00:38.331 --> 00:00:40.959
Lilac. lavender and honey.

10
00:00:42.002 --> 00:00:44.838
- [Maghra sighs]
- You'll make the most appealing bride.

11
00:00:45.881 --> 00:00:46.882
Leave that.

12
00:00:47.591 --> 00:00:50.427
Princess. you must be completely
unadorned for the marriage ceremony.

13
00:00:50.510 --> 00:00:53.555
- No. I will not remove this cuff.
- It's the law of the land.

14
00:00:53.638 --> 00:00:56.016
Handmaiden. what is your name?

15
00:00:57.309 --> 00:00:58.852
Harmony. Your Majesty.

16
00:00:58.935 --> 00:01:01.646
Harmony? That is
a beautiful name.

17
00:01:03.106 --> 00:01:04.481
Give me your hand. Harmony.

18
00:01:04.565 --> 00:01:06.818
[bells jingling]

19
00:01:10.488 --> 00:01:11.990
Harmony.

20
00:01:12.657 --> 00:01:16.161
are you in the habit of telling
princesses what they may and may not do?

21
00:01:16.244 --> 00:01:19.247
Perhaps you would tell
your queen as well?

22
00:01:19.331 --> 00:01:21.249
[gasps] No. Your Majesty. never.

23
00:01:21.333 --> 00:01:23.001
Then hush and leave her.

24
00:01:28.256 --> 00:01:32.552
Hmm. The princess is fully
slathered. You may go. Harmony.

25
00:01:32.636 --> 00:01:33.678
Yes. Your Majesty.

26
00:01:36.556 --> 00:01:37.599
[sighs]

27
00:01:42.938 --> 00:01:44.064
[door closes]

28
00:01:44.147 --> 00:01:47.734
The Pennsan people. and
that means all of them.

29
00:01:47.817 --> 00:01:52.864
even insignificant servants. must
believe this is a true union.

30
00:01:52.948 --> 00:01:55.283
Don't worry. I
will play my part.

31
00:01:55.367 --> 00:01:57.077
You're not in this alone.

32
00:01:57.160 --> 00:02:00.789
Yes. I am. You are not
the one being unfaithful.

33
00:02:02.582 --> 00:02:03.625
[sighs]

34
00:02:04.834 --> 00:02:07.504
This marriage will serve us all.

35
00:02:08.087 --> 00:02:11.007
When your children are found
and brought here to you.

36
00:02:11.091 --> 00:02:13.635
it'll be this arrangement
that'll keep them safe.

37
00:02:14.511 --> 00:02:17.889
[tuning fork echoes]

38
00:02:19.099 --> 00:02:22.269
Some people would be insulted
by their sister tuning them out.

39
00:02:22.352 --> 00:02:24.771
Sibeth. you can
never be silenced.

40
00:02:24.854 --> 00:02:26.398
God knows I've tried.

41
00:02:34.990 --> 00:02:35.991
Here.

42
00:02:38.535 --> 00:02:42.914
Remember when you were little.
and I'd wash your hair?

43
00:03:05.437 --> 00:03:06.688
Don't stop.

44
00:03:11.109 --> 00:03:12.110
Please.

45
00:05:07.893 --> 00:05:10.979
Can you please just...
just stay back?

46
00:05:11.062 --> 00:05:13.690
I promise you. no one is
going to kill me on this path.

47
00:05:13.773 --> 00:05:15.901
Yeah. well. not with
me here. they're not.

48
00:05:15.984 --> 00:05:19.070
Haniwa. Haniwa. wait for me.

49
00:05:19.154 --> 00:05:21.740
[grunts. sighs]

50
00:05:21.823 --> 00:05:27.787
Listen. there's no harm in having
a... a dedicated warrior by your side.

51
00:05:27.871 --> 00:05:30.081
I know I'm grateful for
you and your arrows.

52
00:05:32.876 --> 00:05:34.336
I can hear you thinking.

53
00:05:35.295 --> 00:05:36.379
[scoffs]

54
00:05:38.506 --> 00:05:41.259
Yesterday. I was
mourning my mother.

55
00:05:42.177 --> 00:05:44.221
Today. she is a living princess.

56
00:05:44.888 --> 00:05:48.558
and I am thinking back on
every moment of my childhood.

57
00:05:49.351 --> 00:05:52.145
wondering what was
true and what still is.

58
00:05:54.481 --> 00:05:56.233
We will know soon. my love.

59
00:05:57.275 --> 00:05:58.652
Not soon enough.

60
00:06:00.612 --> 00:06:01.780
[Paris groans]

61
00:06:02.572 --> 00:06:03.657
[sighs. exclaims]

62
00:06:04.699 --> 00:06:07.619
You know. uh. I'm
not a threat to you.

63
00:06:10.247 --> 00:06:12.749
You mistake my
contempt for fear.

64
00:06:15.710 --> 00:06:20.507
Tell me. Witchfinder General.
how many lives have you taken?

65
00:06:21.758 --> 00:06:25.011
Enough to damn my
soul many times over.

66
00:06:26.930 --> 00:06:30.225
And yet. you will kill the
queen whom you have served.

67
00:06:31.768 --> 00:06:34.062
There is not enough
damnation for you.

68
00:06:35.188 --> 00:06:38.233
No. I suspect not.

69
00:06:39.734 --> 00:06:42.028
[panting]

70
00:06:45.240 --> 00:06:46.408
Mmm.

71
00:06:46.491 --> 00:06:49.327
- Are you all right?
- Yeah. I'm fine.

72
00:06:50.495 --> 00:06:54.165
- We should've stayed another night.
- Nah. it's nothing.

73
00:06:55.250 --> 00:06:58.295
If your head fell off. you would
pick it up and carry it to Pennsa.

74
00:06:59.254 --> 00:07:01.381
No. I would make you carry it.

75
00:07:01.464 --> 00:07:03.925
- [chuckles]
- [chuckles] Ouch.

76
00:07:04.009 --> 00:07:06.261
[banging]

77
00:07:06.344 --> 00:07:08.096
These brave soldiers died

78
00:07:08.179 --> 00:07:12.767
trying to stop the murderer. Baba
Voss. from escaping Trivantes.

79
00:07:13.435 --> 00:07:16.396
They died heroes. and
they will be avenged.

80
00:07:16.479 --> 00:07:17.814
[sobbing]

81
00:07:17.898 --> 00:07:20.525
A valiant soldier of the
republic remembered forever.

82
00:07:21.818 --> 00:07:25.447
A sacred son of Trivantes.
now one with us.

83
00:07:26.239 --> 00:07:27.991
[woman crying]

84
00:07:33.872 --> 00:07:36.374
[woman] Rendayo. My son.

85
00:07:42.923 --> 00:07:44.049
Madame Orrie.

86
00:07:45.800 --> 00:07:48.178
Rendayo was a
patriot and a hero.

87
00:07:48.261 --> 00:07:49.554
[sniffling]

88
00:07:49.638 --> 00:07:53.516
I immensely admired him
as if he were my own son.

89
00:07:56.019 --> 00:08:00.273
Those responsible for his death
will suffer. You have my word.

90
00:08:01.274 --> 00:08:04.778
[woman cries]

91
00:08:12.160 --> 00:08:13.161
[sniffles]

92
00:08:16.081 --> 00:08:21.503
[crying]

93
00:08:33.682 --> 00:08:35.225
You have news for me?

94
00:08:35.308 --> 00:08:39.104
Yes. General Voss. A
Witchfinder looking for asylum.

95
00:08:39.187 --> 00:08:40.355
A Witchfinder.

96
00:08:40.438 --> 00:08:42.274
If true. this will
be the first time

97
00:08:42.356 --> 00:08:44.401
one of Tamacti Jun's
soldiers has broken ranks.

98
00:08:46.778 --> 00:08:47.988
What is he trading?

99
00:08:48.071 --> 00:08:50.907
He insists he will
speak only to you.

100
00:08:50.991 --> 00:08:51.992
Ah.

101
00:08:52.659 --> 00:08:54.661
And he will likely regret that.

102
00:08:55.161 --> 00:08:56.162
Bring him to me.

103
00:08:57.330 --> 00:09:00.333
- [guard] Come on.
- [grunting. groaning]

104
00:09:07.007 --> 00:09:12.429
I am Commander General Edo Voss. and
I understand you wish to speak to me.

105
00:09:12.512 --> 00:09:13.513
Yes. sir.

106
00:09:13.597 --> 00:09:16.433
You are the first of the queen's
Witchfinders that I've met

107
00:09:16.516 --> 00:09:20.353
that wasn't already impaled
on the end of my sword.

108
00:09:20.979 --> 00:09:22.898
I have information
you will want. sir.

109
00:09:24.441 --> 00:09:29.613
And why would I trust a soldier
who betrays his own kingdom?

110
00:09:29.696 --> 00:09:32.824
My kingdom is no longer the
kingdom I swore to defend.

111
00:09:33.325 --> 00:09:34.451
And how's that?

112
00:09:35.035 --> 00:09:36.870
I am sworn to protect
the Payan kingdom

113
00:09:36.953 --> 00:09:39.039
from the evils of
witchcraft and therefore...

114
00:09:39.122 --> 00:09:42.417
I am familiar with
Witchfinders. boy.

115
00:09:42.500 --> 00:09:45.545
Including those who might have sight
or seek to facilitate its return.

116
00:09:46.421 --> 00:09:49.299
[Edo Voss] And now. your
queen decrees that the sighted

117
00:09:49.382 --> 00:09:51.218
are. in fact. not witches.

118
00:09:52.969 --> 00:09:54.846
[stammers] Yes. sir.

119
00:09:54.930 --> 00:10:00.185
In fact. she also claims to be carrying
a sighted child in her own womb.

120
00:10:01.311 --> 00:10:02.312
Yes. sir.

121
00:10:02.395 --> 00:10:08.693
Boy. did you really desert your
own army and face certain death

122
00:10:08.777 --> 00:10:13.323
to come here and tell me something
my spies reported days ago?

123
00:10:15.659 --> 00:10:19.079
- Hobble him and sell him to the Slavers.
- [Dax] No. no.

124
00:10:19.162 --> 00:10:20.497
- [guard] Come on.
- Sir.

125
00:10:21.289 --> 00:10:23.959
- Commander Voss. there are others.
- [Edo Voss] Stop!

126
00:10:35.178 --> 00:10:36.179
Others?

127
00:10:37.222 --> 00:10:41.017
Hers won't be the first sighted
child within the Payan royal family.

128
00:10:41.560 --> 00:10:43.562
There are two. already grown.

129
00:10:47.691 --> 00:10:49.651
And these children
already grown…

130
00:10:51.653 --> 00:10:55.782
is one of them a
girl called Haniwa?

131
00:10:57.325 --> 00:10:58.326
[Dax] Yes.

132
00:11:00.787 --> 00:11:01.788
[Edo Voss] Mmm.

133
00:11:32.068 --> 00:11:33.445
So. this is Pennsa?

134
00:11:36.197 --> 00:11:37.198
Yes.

135
00:11:46.583 --> 00:11:47.918
Is it always this quiet?

136
00:11:49.920 --> 00:11:53.089
[sighs] No. Never.

137
00:11:56.593 --> 00:11:57.677
Something's wrong.

138
00:12:07.729 --> 00:12:09.189
There's soldiers ahead.

139
00:12:12.776 --> 00:12:14.527
Stay here and say nothing.

140
00:12:15.528 --> 00:12:18.490
- Uh. should we be worried?
- Not we. you.

141
00:12:39.678 --> 00:12:41.846
- [horse nickers]
- [Toad sighs]

142
00:12:43.098 --> 00:12:45.850
- This is gonna be tricky.
- Why? Isn't my mother here?

143
00:12:45.934 --> 00:12:48.353
- She's here.
- So. what's the problem?

144
00:12:49.354 --> 00:12:51.273
The thing of it is… [sighs]

145
00:12:51.356 --> 00:12:53.275
…she's apparently
getting married today.

146
00:13:10.208 --> 00:13:11.376
Baba. my love…

147
00:13:13.295 --> 00:13:14.337
forgive me.

148
00:13:16.381 --> 00:13:17.382
[Kofun] Mom?

149
00:13:19.801 --> 00:13:20.801
Mom!

150
00:13:21.469 --> 00:13:22.470
Kofun?

151
00:13:23.430 --> 00:13:27.183
- Mom. Mom! Mom! [chuckles]
- [gasps]

152
00:13:28.685 --> 00:13:32.772
Whew. [gasps] You're alive.

153
00:13:32.856 --> 00:13:34.107
My baby.

154
00:13:35.817 --> 00:13:40.447
Oh. I've searched for you every
day since we were separated.

155
00:13:41.323 --> 00:13:42.908
I never stopped.

156
00:13:42.991 --> 00:13:47.746
Mmm. Mom they said that
you're getting married today.

157
00:13:47.829 --> 00:13:49.748
That can't be true.
can it? [inhales]

158
00:13:50.457 --> 00:13:51.917
I will explain everything.

159
00:13:53.960 --> 00:13:56.254
Where's your father? And Haniwa?

160
00:13:57.589 --> 00:13:59.758
He went into Trivantes
to get her back.

161
00:13:59.841 --> 00:14:00.842
Trivantes?

162
00:14:00.926 --> 00:14:03.011
- [knocking]
- [Harmony] Princess Maghra. it's time.

163
00:14:03.094 --> 00:14:06.640
Wait. Why... Why Trivantes?

164
00:14:06.723 --> 00:14:09.368
- What happened with Jerlamarel?
- How can you be getting married today?

165
00:14:09.392 --> 00:14:11.454
[Harmony] Lord Harlan is waiting.
and the queen is growing impatient.

166
00:14:11.478 --> 00:14:13.230
- I'm coming.
- Who is Lord Harlan?

167
00:14:13.855 --> 00:14:15.833
I will explain everything
later. I have to go. Kofun.

168
00:14:15.857 --> 00:14:19.402
- I just need you to trust me.
- Mama? [whispers] Mama. you can't do this.

169
00:14:19.486 --> 00:14:21.988
I... I can't stop this.

170
00:14:22.614 --> 00:14:23.674
Your father would understand.

171
00:14:23.698 --> 00:14:27.035
No. I don't think he would understand why
his dead wife is marrying someone else.

172
00:14:27.118 --> 00:14:28.453
- Kofun...
- Stop saying my name

173
00:14:28.536 --> 00:14:30.038
and do something to fix this!

174
00:14:30.121 --> 00:14:33.416
I... I don't know what is happening.
Mama. but you can't go through with it.

175
00:14:33.500 --> 00:14:34.668
Be quiet!

176
00:14:35.502 --> 00:14:39.506
I am still the mother you
knew. and you are still my son.

177
00:14:40.465 --> 00:14:42.259
But things have changed.

178
00:14:43.802 --> 00:14:46.846
Now. I'm doing this for
you and for all of us.

179
00:14:48.056 --> 00:14:51.184
So you stay here. You
stay here in my room.

180
00:14:51.851 --> 00:14:53.311
and you speak to no one.

181
00:14:54.563 --> 00:14:58.149
and then we will talk when all
of this is over. I promise.

182
00:15:00.402 --> 00:15:03.321
- I promise.
- [grunts] D-Don't do this.

183
00:15:05.198 --> 00:15:06.700
- Don't do this.
- I have to.

184
00:15:17.252 --> 00:15:20.338
I have so many questions.

185
00:15:21.298 --> 00:15:25.010
[Baba Voss retches.
sniffs. groans]

186
00:15:25.927 --> 00:15:28.722
[coughing]

187
00:15:29.306 --> 00:15:30.932
- [coughs]
- All right. that's enough.

188
00:15:31.016 --> 00:15:33.435
- Ah. I just need a moment. [sighs]
- Paris?

189
00:15:33.518 --> 00:15:35.186
- [Baba Voss grunts]
- [panting]

190
00:15:35.270 --> 00:15:38.064
[Baba Voss grunts. sighs]

191
00:15:38.857 --> 00:15:40.734
- [grunts] Woman.
- Oh!

192
00:15:40.817 --> 00:15:43.236
I feel the fever
through your clothing.

193
00:15:44.070 --> 00:15:46.907
- It's not gonna kill me.
- You need a healer.

194
00:15:47.407 --> 00:15:48.825
We'll find one in Pennsa.

195
00:15:48.909 --> 00:15:51.536
Baba. You'll be dead by
the time we get there.

196
00:15:53.246 --> 00:15:56.166
We are in the Lakelands now.
not far from the Valier.

197
00:15:56.249 --> 00:15:58.585
They will offer us
shelter and a healer.

198
00:15:59.461 --> 00:16:00.462
Papa?

199
00:16:01.755 --> 00:16:04.549
- [sighs]
- Please.

200
00:16:06.551 --> 00:16:07.844
Okay. my love.

201
00:16:08.720 --> 00:16:11.723
[Tamacti Jun] I cannot accompany
you to Valier territory.

202
00:16:12.265 --> 00:16:14.142
Well. that is
where we are going.

203
00:16:14.226 --> 00:16:17.187
Understand. the hidden
tribes were not hidden to me.

204
00:16:18.063 --> 00:16:20.732
The Valier suffered
greatly at my hands.

205
00:16:29.407 --> 00:16:33.745
You stay quiet and camp nearby.
We'll find you on the way out.

206
00:16:35.163 --> 00:16:36.748
[sighs. sniffles]

207
00:16:38.166 --> 00:16:39.251
Or not.

208
00:16:41.211 --> 00:16:42.212
[spits]

209
00:16:42.712 --> 00:16:43.880
[Baba Voss groans]

210
00:17:07.026 --> 00:17:12.949
[Queen Kane. crowd vocalizing]

211
00:17:27.549 --> 00:17:30.927
Our God. beyond
your flame above…

212
00:17:33.013 --> 00:17:35.640
let your will be done
on this special day

213
00:17:35.724 --> 00:17:38.101
in this holiest of unions.

214
00:17:40.103 --> 00:17:43.565
Give guidance. clear paths.

215
00:17:43.648 --> 00:17:49.946
condemn those who trespass against us
to writhe within your fire and smoke.

216
00:17:51.197 --> 00:17:57.370
For Thine is the darkness.
the power and the glory.

217
00:17:58.997 --> 00:18:00.916
Forever and ever.

218
00:18:23.772 --> 00:18:28.068
Princess Maghra and Lord Harlan…

219
00:18:32.697 --> 00:18:35.867
you enter this union
adorned in scented splendor.

220
00:18:43.250 --> 00:18:44.834
[clicks tongue]

221
00:18:48.964 --> 00:18:50.382
[clicks tongue]

222
00:18:56.012 --> 00:18:58.848
You've pledged your
commitment to each other

223
00:18:58.932 --> 00:19:02.060
with the joining of bodies
and souls before God.

224
00:19:03.770 --> 00:19:10.735
So. by the divine ordination bestowed
upon me. you may seal your union.

225
00:19:18.368 --> 00:19:22.998
[cheering]

226
00:19:40.223 --> 00:19:42.058
[bells jingling]

227
00:20:44.287 --> 00:20:45.872
- [woman murmurs]
- Thank you. you too.

228
00:20:47.082 --> 00:20:48.208
- [man shouts]
- [gasps]

229
00:20:49.542 --> 00:20:50.877
[sighs]

230
00:20:51.461 --> 00:20:53.421
Princess Maghra.

231
00:20:55.173 --> 00:20:59.886
- Any wife of Harlan's is a sister of mine.
- Maghra. you remember my brother.

232
00:21:00.595 --> 00:21:04.975
- [Harlan] Thank you.
- Kerrigan. I changed your diapers.

233
00:21:05.559 --> 00:21:08.395
Well. Lucky for all of us.
I have people for that now.

234
00:21:08.478 --> 00:21:10.939
[chuckles. sniffs. grunts]

235
00:21:11.022 --> 00:21:12.691
[chuckles]

236
00:21:12.774 --> 00:21:14.401
- Thank you.
- [Maghra chuckles] Oh.

237
00:21:15.610 --> 00:21:17.779
- [Harlan] Thank you so much.
- Oh.

238
00:21:17.862 --> 00:21:19.864
- I'm sorry. Sorry.
- [Kerrigan] Mmm.

239
00:21:20.907 --> 00:21:23.076
All right. Go. go. Get off. Go.

240
00:21:36.882 --> 00:21:39.259
- [Charlotte] Are we close?
- [Paris] Yes.

241
00:21:39.342 --> 00:21:41.612
Because I don't think the big
one can make it much further.

242
00:21:41.636 --> 00:21:43.322
and I don't think we'll
be able to carry him.

243
00:21:43.346 --> 00:21:44.514
[shushes]

244
00:21:46.683 --> 00:21:48.435
- Who's there?
- [metal scraping]

245
00:21:48.518 --> 00:21:49.561
Make yourself known.

246
00:21:49.644 --> 00:21:52.856
[man] Who enters Valier territory
without announcing themselves?

247
00:21:53.481 --> 00:21:57.694
Brother! We bring no
threat. I am Paris.

248
00:21:57.777 --> 00:21:59.738
We are the last of the Alkenny.

249
00:21:59.821 --> 00:22:03.116
No. I am last of the Alkenny.

250
00:22:04.451 --> 00:22:06.828
- Chet-chet.
- Chet-chet-chet.

251
00:22:06.912 --> 00:22:08.663
Bow! [chuckling. exclaiming]

252
00:22:09.164 --> 00:22:10.248
Lion.

253
00:22:10.332 --> 00:22:15.378
- [Paris] Ah. Bow Lion. [chuckles]
- [chuckles]

254
00:22:15.462 --> 00:22:16.755
[sniffs] Oh. Paris.

255
00:22:44.449 --> 00:22:45.450
[Queen Kane] Kofun?

256
00:22:47.035 --> 00:22:48.411
- Is it you?
- [sword clatters]

257
00:22:50.413 --> 00:22:51.581
It's okay. You're safe.

258
00:22:52.707 --> 00:22:53.750
I'm your Aunt Sibeth.

259
00:22:57.045 --> 00:23:00.465
I was overjoyed when I
heard you were finally here.

260
00:23:00.549 --> 00:23:03.260
We've been waiting such
a long time for you.

261
00:23:04.427 --> 00:23:07.180
[bells jingling]

262
00:23:12.602 --> 00:23:13.812
Will you embrace me?

263
00:23:24.781 --> 00:23:27.784
[gasping]

264
00:23:29.327 --> 00:23:30.412
[gasps]

265
00:23:36.710 --> 00:23:38.461
You're taller than your parents.

266
00:23:41.464 --> 00:23:44.968
Would you like something? Anything
to drink? I'll send for it.

267
00:23:45.051 --> 00:23:47.596
No. Thank you.

268
00:23:49.139 --> 00:23:52.350
How tragic we're only meeting
now for the first time.

269
00:23:54.519 --> 00:23:56.354
You hunted us my whole life.

270
00:24:00.442 --> 00:24:02.819
If only Maghra had
announced herself long ago.

271
00:24:02.903 --> 00:24:06.072
I would've protected
her. protected you.

272
00:24:07.157 --> 00:24:08.366
She knew that.

273
00:24:09.576 --> 00:24:12.621
We were hunting Jerlamarel
and his children.

274
00:24:12.704 --> 00:24:14.372
I didn't know they
were Maghra's.

275
00:24:15.081 --> 00:24:18.835
I'd been led to believe
Jerlamarel had killed my sister.

276
00:24:18.919 --> 00:24:20.212
I believed him to be the devil.

277
00:24:20.295 --> 00:24:23.465
You know that's not true.
Why'd my mother stay hidden?

278
00:24:24.966 --> 00:24:26.509
Whatever mistakes she made.

279
00:24:27.636 --> 00:24:31.056
I'm sure she made them to
keep you and your sister safe.

280
00:24:31.681 --> 00:24:33.350
which is what I'm
trying to do right now.

281
00:24:33.433 --> 00:24:35.894
Well. even with your decree.

282
00:24:35.977 --> 00:24:38.480
people in Paya still believe
a witch is to be burned.

283
00:24:38.563 --> 00:24:40.690
I've been known to
change a few minds.

284
00:24:41.691 --> 00:24:43.568
It might take a bit of time.

285
00:24:43.652 --> 00:24:48.990
but the Payans will
learn. as I have.

286
00:24:50.784 --> 00:24:54.162
to embrace those with
sight as blessed.

287
00:24:59.668 --> 00:25:01.253
How difficult for you.

288
00:25:02.754 --> 00:25:06.466
journeying to this place. arriving
on your mother's wedding day.

289
00:25:07.092 --> 00:25:08.718
The world must seem upside down.

290
00:25:10.887 --> 00:25:12.430
But know this.

291
00:25:13.223 --> 00:25:17.394
no one shall stand against you.
not while you're in my kingdom.

292
00:25:18.645 --> 00:25:20.188
Do you believe me?

293
00:25:24.317 --> 00:25:25.318
I don't know.

294
00:25:26.861 --> 00:25:27.904
I want to.

295
00:25:29.864 --> 00:25:30.991
Fair enough.

296
00:25:32.158 --> 00:25:35.620
Many good things
start with… desire.

297
00:25:36.454 --> 00:25:38.582
[inhales]

298
00:25:40.250 --> 00:25:42.419
- [chuckles]
- [breathes heavily]

299
00:25:44.004 --> 00:25:47.215
I've arranged a room for
you. We'll talk again soon?

300
00:26:05.317 --> 00:26:07.986
[Edo Voss] Queen Kane's war
council is mobilizing her armies.

301
00:26:08.486 --> 00:26:11.781
And we've learned from
the Payan defector

302
00:26:11.865 --> 00:26:13.992
that not only has
Princess Maghra returned.

303
00:26:14.618 --> 00:26:17.495
but she comes with two grown
children. Haniwa and Kofun.

304
00:26:18.788 --> 00:26:19.998
Both sighted.

305
00:26:20.081 --> 00:26:23.168
The Payan fanatics will
burn them at the stake.

306
00:26:24.127 --> 00:26:25.980
[Edo Voss] They will do
as their queen commands.

307
00:26:26.004 --> 00:26:28.965
With two sighted children in
the royal family now of age.

308
00:26:29.674 --> 00:26:31.343
they are an even greater threat.

309
00:26:31.426 --> 00:26:33.595
[The Military] We don't
know their intentions.

310
00:26:33.678 --> 00:26:34.822
We know they took the trouble

311
00:26:34.846 --> 00:26:37.265
to break their Witchfinder
General out of captivity.

312
00:26:38.058 --> 00:26:40.518
That is intention enough.
We must strike now.

313
00:26:40.602 --> 00:26:44.481
It would be suicide for
the Payans to attack us.

314
00:26:45.732 --> 00:26:49.027
The queen may be crazy.
but she's not a fool.

315
00:26:49.110 --> 00:26:52.072
Still. these are
troubling developments.

316
00:26:53.156 --> 00:26:54.508
I can muster our forces
in a matter of d...

317
00:26:54.532 --> 00:26:55.825
No. steady. Edo.

318
00:26:56.743 --> 00:27:00.247
The Ganites are still
raining shit on us out west.

319
00:27:00.330 --> 00:27:03.333
And you yourself stood here and
heard the council's attitude

320
00:27:03.416 --> 00:27:04.960
about an eastern campaign.

321
00:27:05.043 --> 00:27:08.380
- You will never sell it.
- No. You will do that.

322
00:27:08.463 --> 00:27:10.674
[The Military] You
overestimate my influence.

323
00:27:10.757 --> 00:27:13.051
I am but one third
of the Triangle.

324
00:27:14.928 --> 00:27:15.929
But still.

325
00:27:16.638 --> 00:27:21.101
I will convince the council to request
a diplomatic summit with the Payans.

326
00:27:21.184 --> 00:27:24.688
- Trivantians do not sue for peace!
- We do what we need to do.

327
00:27:25.480 --> 00:27:28.316
And you will do as
ordered. Do you understand?

328
00:27:31.611 --> 00:27:32.737
Yes. sir.

329
00:27:32.821 --> 00:27:36.783
If for nothing else. it will give us
time to bring a battalion or two east.

330
00:27:36.866 --> 00:27:39.244
if it comes to that.

331
00:27:39.911 --> 00:27:41.204
Understood.

332
00:27:44.624 --> 00:27:48.086
I will let you know what
the council decides.

333
00:28:03.518 --> 00:28:07.689
[Bow Lion] Breathe slow and
deep. Baba. and drink this.

334
00:28:07.772 --> 00:28:11.401
[tapping cup]

335
00:28:11.484 --> 00:28:13.445
- It will give you strength.
- [sighs]

336
00:28:19.951 --> 00:28:22.329
[groans] When did
you become a healer?

337
00:28:23.622 --> 00:28:27.459
I'm not yet. but I've been
learning from the healers here.

338
00:28:30.253 --> 00:28:33.590
Those roots should absorb the
infections so that the fever can pass.

339
00:28:34.841 --> 00:28:38.553
You've lost so much.
all because of us.

340
00:28:40.597 --> 00:28:41.932
Still. you take us in.

341
00:28:46.394 --> 00:28:47.938
[Bow Lion] We are
one tribe. remember?

342
00:28:52.609 --> 00:28:53.860
Yeah. I remember.

343
00:29:23.932 --> 00:29:26.935
[breathing heavily]

344
00:29:38.321 --> 00:29:39.531
[bells jingling]

345
00:29:40.448 --> 00:29:41.449
[Maghra] Kofun?

346
00:29:42.409 --> 00:29:44.244
[Harlan] No. Not Kofun.

347
00:29:46.496 --> 00:29:48.039
[Maghra] What are
you doing in here?

348
00:29:48.707 --> 00:29:52.168
Maghra. it's our wedding night.
Where else am I gonna be?

349
00:29:53.587 --> 00:29:55.505
[bells jingling]

350
00:29:55.589 --> 00:29:58.258
This is not a marriage.
This is an alliance.

351
00:29:58.758 --> 00:30:01.928
Right. but... but
it can be both.

352
00:30:06.850 --> 00:30:09.311
Put on your pants.
Harlan. I need your help.

353
00:30:11.146 --> 00:30:12.355
- Now.
- Fine.

354
00:30:14.941 --> 00:30:15.942
[Harlan grunts]

355
00:30:31.374 --> 00:30:33.376
[tapping]

356
00:30:36.922 --> 00:30:39.299
They made me sneak you
some pheasant and ale.

357
00:30:40.008 --> 00:30:42.761
Don't worry. I didn't poison it.
if that's what you're thinking.

358
00:30:44.971 --> 00:30:46.306
I had no such thought.

359
00:30:47.015 --> 00:30:48.850
And I had no such poison.

360
00:30:48.934 --> 00:30:50.101
[plate clatters]

361
00:30:50.185 --> 00:30:51.645
[liquid sloshes]

362
00:30:53.313 --> 00:30:55.607
[Andal] Our Alkenny
brothers and sisters.

363
00:30:55.690 --> 00:30:58.443
last time you came to
us. we turned you away.

364
00:30:58.985 --> 00:31:02.697
You healed our Bow Lion. It is
more than we could've hoped for.

365
00:31:02.781 --> 00:31:06.451
It is you who bring us a message
of hope upon your return.

366
00:31:06.910 --> 00:31:09.371
We feared that you would
lead Witchfinders to us.

367
00:31:09.454 --> 00:31:13.792
because when they had come prior. they
said the sighted hid amongst the Alkenny.

368
00:31:14.376 --> 00:31:15.436
- [swords clashing]
- [women screaming]

369
00:31:15.460 --> 00:31:19.381
They slaughtered
men. women. children.

370
00:31:20.632 --> 00:31:22.425
Their blades didn't
discriminate.

371
00:31:23.468 --> 00:31:26.763
all because the Witchfinders
believed we had knowledge of witches.

372
00:31:26.846 --> 00:31:27.681
[screams echoing]

373
00:31:27.764 --> 00:31:30.809
Those of us who lived were
spared only to spread the fear.

374
00:31:33.311 --> 00:31:37.315
But we will rebuild. We're
already making babies.

375
00:31:38.149 --> 00:31:43.029
We will make ourselves whole to honor
the memory of the many that were lost.

376
00:31:43.113 --> 00:31:45.991
[screams echoing]

377
00:31:46.074 --> 00:31:47.158
Stop!

378
00:31:49.828 --> 00:31:54.207
[Andal] And now word comes that the queen
will no longer send her Witchfinders.

379
00:31:54.291 --> 00:31:56.418
as she no longer
searches for witches.

380
00:31:58.712 --> 00:32:00.755
The queen may yet
change her mind.

381
00:32:00.839 --> 00:32:06.928
but tonight. we celebrate your escape
from Trivantes and savor our freedom…

382
00:32:07.012 --> 00:32:08.638
[signaling] Tamacti Jun is here.

383
00:32:08.722 --> 00:32:11.975
…however short-lived. from the
queen and her Witchfinders.

384
00:32:12.058 --> 00:32:13.351
[tapping]

385
00:32:13.435 --> 00:32:15.770
[Andal] These are
uncertain times.

386
00:32:15.854 --> 00:32:17.856
but we face them with hope

387
00:32:17.939 --> 00:32:21.026
for a future more
peaceful than our past.

388
00:32:22.986 --> 00:32:24.446
[grunts]

389
00:32:25.614 --> 00:32:27.490
- Have you lost your mind?
- [grunts]

390
00:32:28.491 --> 00:32:32.203
The Valier deserve retribution.
I owe 'em that much.

391
00:32:32.287 --> 00:32:33.887
[Baba Voss] No. you
owe me. Witchfinder.

392
00:32:33.955 --> 00:32:37.584
You think I don't wanna rip your throat
out every time I hear your voice?

393
00:32:39.461 --> 00:32:41.171
You slaughtered my people too.

394
00:32:42.923 --> 00:32:44.507
But you do not get to die.

395
00:32:45.508 --> 00:32:48.220
Your punishment is you will
live with what you have done.

396
00:32:52.140 --> 00:32:55.936
Death must be earned too. Witchfinder.
every bit as much as life.

397
00:32:56.019 --> 00:32:58.855
[breathes heavily]

398
00:33:19.793 --> 00:33:21.378
That's his favorite spot.

399
00:33:23.088 --> 00:33:26.758
And… his favorite chair.

400
00:33:28.051 --> 00:33:29.803
- Kerrigan. Come on.
- [groans]

401
00:33:29.886 --> 00:33:31.221
Wake the fuck up. Come on.

402
00:33:33.056 --> 00:33:36.851
[sniffs] Princess. [sighs]

403
00:33:36.935 --> 00:33:38.979
I can still smell
the blossoms on you.

404
00:33:39.938 --> 00:33:43.608
You two should be home. rolling
around in sticky sheets.

405
00:33:43.692 --> 00:33:44.859
I need your help.

406
00:33:44.943 --> 00:33:49.447
- Brother. not up to the task?
- We need you to cross the border.

407
00:33:52.033 --> 00:33:53.451
What's the cargo?

408
00:33:54.035 --> 00:33:55.537
Her daughter. Haniwa.

409
00:33:57.038 --> 00:33:58.999
She's being held by
the Trivantian army.

410
00:34:00.166 --> 00:34:01.751
- Oh.
- Yeah.

411
00:34:02.460 --> 00:34:03.670
Yeah. fuck off.

412
00:34:04.337 --> 00:34:05.630
Please.

413
00:34:05.714 --> 00:34:09.384
[Kerrigan] Princess.
generally in my trade.

414
00:34:09.467 --> 00:34:12.470
the object is to avoid the
military. not go searching for them.

415
00:34:12.554 --> 00:34:13.805
Kerrigan.

416
00:34:13.889 --> 00:34:16.349
[breathes heavily]

417
00:34:20.936 --> 00:34:24.941
If she really is in a military brig.
I won't be able to get her out.

418
00:34:25.025 --> 00:34:29.237
Come on. Prison guards can be
bought. same as anybody else.

419
00:34:29.320 --> 00:34:30.614
[Kerrigan] Maybe.

420
00:34:30.697 --> 00:34:33.240
But it would take
a lot of copper.

421
00:34:33.325 --> 00:34:34.617
For you or for them?

422
00:34:35.994 --> 00:34:38.704
- I am offended. Princess.
- No. he's not.

423
00:34:40.248 --> 00:34:44.211
No. I suppose I'm not. Still.
it would take some doing.

424
00:34:44.711 --> 00:34:48.131
When you find her. how will you
get her safely out of Trivantes?

425
00:34:49.132 --> 00:34:51.194
[Kerrigan] Ah. getting out
of the city's the easy part.

426
00:34:51.218 --> 00:34:55.931
I have been smuggling Ganite thornflower
from Trivantes to Pennsa for years.

427
00:34:58.642 --> 00:35:04.856
I know every hole and tunnel
into and out of that place.

428
00:35:04.940 --> 00:35:07.442
- [inhales. groans]
- So you'll do it?

429
00:35:10.695 --> 00:35:16.409
[inhales] Uh. consider
it. um. a wedding gift.

430
00:35:18.036 --> 00:35:19.329
[yawns]

431
00:35:19.412 --> 00:35:22.040
I'll leave when the
God Flame warms.

432
00:35:22.123 --> 00:35:23.792
- [Kerrigan yawns]
- You'll leave now.

433
00:35:24.542 --> 00:35:27.045
[kisses] Come on. Up you get.

434
00:36:04.124 --> 00:36:06.418
[Paris] No. Now is not the time.

435
00:36:09.045 --> 00:36:11.548
Paris? How could
you bring him here?

436
00:36:11.631 --> 00:36:14.092
How could you even share
the air that he breathes?

437
00:36:14.175 --> 00:36:16.845
We need him. He
has a new purpose.

438
00:36:16.928 --> 00:36:20.140
No. He dies by my hand tonight.

439
00:36:21.516 --> 00:36:23.602
[breathes shakily]
He killed my mother.

440
00:36:23.685 --> 00:36:26.855
Yes. Time will come
he pays for that.

441
00:36:27.731 --> 00:36:29.357
I can't believe this is you.

442
00:36:31.109 --> 00:36:32.193
You're a traitor.

443
00:36:32.736 --> 00:36:35.322
He is our only hope
of getting to Maghra.

444
00:36:35.405 --> 00:36:37.824
The Witchfinders
massacred the Valier.

445
00:36:39.451 --> 00:36:41.131
They will have something
to say about this.

446
00:36:41.202 --> 00:36:45.081
Please. You cannot
tell them. You cannot.

447
00:36:47.250 --> 00:36:50.378
- I trusted you. I trusted you.
- Bow Lion. Bow Lion.

448
00:36:51.963 --> 00:36:52.964
You know me.

449
00:36:54.466 --> 00:36:56.718
You know my heart.

450
00:36:59.429 --> 00:37:00.889
- Girl.
- [cries]

451
00:37:03.516 --> 00:37:06.186
[Bow Lion sniffles] Be gone
before God Flame rises.

452
00:37:08.939 --> 00:37:11.233
I won't keep your secret
any longer than that.

453
00:37:38.218 --> 00:37:39.219
Kofun?

454
00:37:40.637 --> 00:37:42.430
[snapping]

455
00:37:45.141 --> 00:37:48.144
[sighs] Thank God Flame.

456
00:37:48.228 --> 00:37:49.563
[sighs]

457
00:37:50.105 --> 00:37:52.524
- I told you to stay in my room.
- I know.

458
00:37:53.483 --> 00:37:58.029
- I'm here.
- [Maghra breathes deeply]

459
00:37:58.613 --> 00:37:59.781
I'm sorry.

460
00:38:01.866 --> 00:38:06.204
I know this must all feel very
strange and upsetting to you.

461
00:38:06.288 --> 00:38:08.832
and I promise you I
will explain everything.

462
00:38:09.416 --> 00:38:12.210
but you cannot disobey
me like that again.

463
00:38:12.294 --> 00:38:13.670
It is not safe here.

464
00:38:14.796 --> 00:38:16.756
- My sister is someone who...
- Sibeth.

465
00:38:18.717 --> 00:38:20.427
Don't worry. We've met.

466
00:38:22.053 --> 00:38:24.139
She came to see me
after your wedding.

467
00:38:28.018 --> 00:38:29.060
Kofun.

468
00:38:31.938 --> 00:38:34.149
- You cannot trust her.
- [Kofun] Why not?

469
00:38:35.317 --> 00:38:37.736
She's not the one who
lied to me my entire life.

470
00:38:38.737 --> 00:38:39.738
[sighs]

471
00:38:40.822 --> 00:38:42.324
It is not that simple.

472
00:38:42.407 --> 00:38:43.742
[snaps]

473
00:38:43.825 --> 00:38:45.577
You betrayed your
husband tonight.

474
00:38:46.870 --> 00:38:49.831
You betrayed all of us and
not for the first time.

475
00:38:51.249 --> 00:38:55.086
You could've identified yourself to
the Witchfinders when we were babies.

476
00:38:55.629 --> 00:38:57.839
You could've saved the Alkenny.

477
00:38:57.923 --> 00:38:59.692
We wouldn't have had to spend
our entire lives running.

478
00:38:59.716 --> 00:39:03.845
My sister would never have accepted any
sighted children that weren't her own.

479
00:39:05.472 --> 00:39:07.766
She would've killed all of us.

480
00:39:07.849 --> 00:39:10.352
I was trying to protect you
the best way I knew how.

481
00:39:10.435 --> 00:39:12.604
- By lying to us.
- Of course by lying to you.

482
00:39:12.687 --> 00:39:14.457
The truth would've gotten
you burned at the stake.

483
00:39:14.481 --> 00:39:15.482
No.

484
00:39:16.483 --> 00:39:21.821
You resented us. You resented
our sight. You always have.

485
00:39:22.822 --> 00:39:25.867
That's why you were so angry when
you realized we'd learned to read.

486
00:39:27.202 --> 00:39:28.203
Wasn't it?

487
00:39:29.871 --> 00:39:34.000
You wouldn't speak to us. We'd
become unrecognizable you said.

488
00:39:34.751 --> 00:39:37.212
Do you recognize yourself. Mama?

489
00:39:39.506 --> 00:39:40.674
Because I don't.

490
00:39:42.092 --> 00:39:46.555
You and Haniwa belong to a world
that I couldn't begin to understand.

491
00:39:48.265 --> 00:39:51.643
I was terrified that one day
it would take you away from me.

492
00:39:55.981 --> 00:39:57.274
Looks like it did.

493
00:40:03.071 --> 00:40:04.823
What are you doing
about Haniwa and Dad?

494
00:40:07.993 --> 00:40:10.370
Lord Harlan has already
sent someone to find them.

495
00:40:12.455 --> 00:40:13.456
[scoffs]

496
00:40:15.208 --> 00:40:17.085
[laughs]

497
00:40:17.168 --> 00:40:20.505
Right. I'm sure your new husband is
very determined to find your old one.

498
00:40:44.279 --> 00:40:48.909
[Tamacti Jun sniffs. exhales]

499
00:40:54.247 --> 00:40:58.585
You asked me if I remember
how many I had killed.

500
00:41:02.339 --> 00:41:05.759
That's like me asking you how
many breaths you took today.

501
00:41:21.483 --> 00:41:25.445
When the queen left
me bleeding to death…

502
00:41:28.114 --> 00:41:29.908
I fell into a state.

503
00:41:31.910 --> 00:41:35.997
Not dead… but no longer
among the living.

504
00:41:40.293 --> 00:41:41.753
And it was there…

505
00:41:43.630 --> 00:41:44.839
suddenly…

506
00:41:47.634 --> 00:41:48.969
I had vision.

507
00:41:52.305 --> 00:41:54.516
[sniffs] Do you know what I saw?

508
00:42:01.231 --> 00:42:02.649
I saw faces.

509
00:42:05.151 --> 00:42:08.446
I saw the faces…

510
00:42:09.072 --> 00:42:14.786
of every man. woman and child
that I had murdered and tortured.

511
00:42:18.790 --> 00:42:20.333
I heard their screams.

512
00:42:23.044 --> 00:42:24.796
I could feel their pain.

513
00:42:30.343 --> 00:42:33.054
But in all of those faces…

514
00:42:35.682 --> 00:42:41.354
I could not find that of
my wife nor of my children.

515
00:42:46.276 --> 00:42:52.490
I was not there when Queen Kane
drowned them in their beds.

516
00:42:59.664 --> 00:43:00.916
Instead…

517
00:43:03.835 --> 00:43:08.423
I was butchering
all those faces.

518
00:43:11.218 --> 00:43:16.097
For years and years. you
have fought for darkness.

519
00:43:19.392 --> 00:43:22.229
Now you must fight for light.

520
00:43:26.816 --> 00:43:29.236
You should not have
stopped the girl.

521
00:43:35.242 --> 00:43:36.243
[grunts]

522
00:43:36.826 --> 00:43:40.914
All right. No more stopping.
We walk until we reach Pennsa.

523
00:43:41.873 --> 00:43:42.874
Do not fear.

524
00:43:44.709 --> 00:43:48.505
You will have plenty of
opportunities to die.

525
00:43:48.588 --> 00:43:49.631
[sniffs]

526
00:43:50.298 --> 00:43:51.508
We all will.

527
00:43:54.010 --> 00:43:58.431
[Haniwa] I always thought that the
fact that I could see and you couldn't

528
00:43:59.224 --> 00:44:01.059
was something that separated us.

529
00:44:02.727 --> 00:44:04.938
Thought there was so
much space between us.

530
00:44:05.564 --> 00:44:09.651
But every time I feel
like I'm beyond help.

531
00:44:10.860 --> 00:44:16.074
in the House of Enlightenment. in
Trivantes. somehow you always find me.

532
00:44:19.536 --> 00:44:24.249
You're my baby girl. Kofun
is my boy. Maghra my wife.

533
00:44:25.125 --> 00:44:29.671
As long as I'm alive. nothing
will separate us. Yes.

534
00:44:33.800 --> 00:44:35.385
I know I don't make it easy.

535
00:44:38.305 --> 00:44:39.514
No. you don't.

536
00:44:41.224 --> 00:44:43.101
From this place. it's
two days to Pennsa.

537
00:44:45.770 --> 00:44:48.273
What do you think it
will be like. Pennsa?

538
00:44:50.108 --> 00:44:51.109
Crowded.

539
00:44:52.444 --> 00:44:55.071
[chuckles] What do you
think she'll be like?

540
00:44:56.448 --> 00:44:58.867
- Uh. she'll be like Maghra.
- Right.

541
00:45:00.785 --> 00:45:02.704
Do we even know who that is?
